                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1042">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6311/211</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PFC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1042fn1">So addressed in error; the next day an
                        identic telegram (No. 105) was sent to the Minister in Denmark, and the
                        Ambassador in Austria-Hungary was directed to take no action (telegram No.
                        1227). See File No. 701.6311/210.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-16T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1226. Your 250, May 15. Explain that it would be physically impossible for United
                    States to send a warship at this time for the purpose indicated. I have no
                    doubt, however, if requested to do so, that the Department can make arrangements
                    for the safe-conduct to the United States of an ambassador from
                    Austria-Hungary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
